Thanks for the detailed repro.

This is a known interaction between the HTML `<canvas>` element's intrinsic sizing and CSS percentage-based heights in flexbox layouts. The `<canvas>` element is inline by default, and SkiaSharp sets its HTML `width`/`height` attributes (for the drawing buffer resolution), which changes the intrinsic size and can interfere with flexbox height calculations.

Here's a workaround you can use: set `display:block` and explicit sizing directly on the SKCanvasView component:

```razor
<SKCanvasView OnPaintSurface="OnPaintSurface"
    style="width:100%; height:100%; display:block;" />
```

Alternatively, use `position: absolute` on the canvas to decouple it from intrinsic size influence:

```css
.canvas-container {
    position: relative;
    flex: 1;
}
.canvas-container canvas {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
}
```

See also #2038 and #2834 for prior discussion of this pattern.
